name        : onix-systemd
version     : @SYSTEMD_VERSION@
release     : 2
summary     : Native source-built systemd userspace for ONIX
license     : LGPL-2.1-or-later
homepage    : https://systemd.io/
upstreams   :
    - @SYSTEMD_NATIVE_PAYLOAD_URL@: @SYSTEMD_NATIVE_PAYLOAD_SHA256@
provides-exclude:
    - '^pkgconfig\(.*\)$'
rundeps-exclude:
    - '^interpreter\(/lib/ld-musl-x86_64\.so\.1\(x86_64\)\)$'
description : |
    Native ONIX systemd userspace payload.

    This recipe draft is the Phase 421 contract for Phase 422. The source build
    happens before boulder packages the prepared payload, following the same
    pattern used by the Phase 409 BusyBox and Phase 412 Dropbear stones.

    The first native package is intentionally allowed to be a monolithic
    bootstrap-native payload. It may carry the immediate musl runtime libraries
    and helper binaries needed to boot. Later ONIX phases can split those pieces
    into smaller dependency stones after the native systemd boot proof exists.

    Required runtime policy:

    - no installed path may point into the old bootstrap store
    - no installed executable may require the old bootstrap store as interpreter
    - systemd must be source-built for ONIX, not wrapped from a prebuilt payload
install     : |
    install -dm00755 %(installroot)
    cp -a usr %(installroot)/

    find %(installroot)/usr -type d -exec chmod 00755 {} \;
    chmod 00755 %(installroot)/usr/lib/systemd/systemd
    chmod 0644 \
        %(installroot)/usr/share/onix/packages/onix-systemd.md \
        %(installroot)/usr/share/onix/packages/onix-systemd.helpers \
        %(installroot)/usr/share/onix/packages/onix-systemd.needed

    # Boulder build dirs inherit setgid. Clear it on directories we created so
    # Moss receives ordinary directory layout metadata.
    find %(installroot)/usr -type d -exec chmod g-s {} \;
